message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The formation of the median umbilical ligament is a result of the obliteration of the urachus, connecting the bladder and the umbilicus during fetal development. Failure of this obliteration can lead to a patent urachus or urinary fistula. Lateral and medial umbilical ligaments are remnants of the umbilical arteries, while the falciform ligament has no relationship to the umbilicus or urinary system.
